headline: Why LGI Homes (LGIH) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of affordable single-family home construction company LGI Homes (NASDAQ:LGIH) fell 3.3% in the afternoon session after the stock fell along with other homebuilders as peer Toll Brothers issued a disappointing forecast for 2026 deliveries. Toll Brothers, a major luxury homebuilder, projected it would deliver between 10,300 and 10,700 homes in 2026, which was below analysts' consensus forecast of 10,843. headline: How Recent Developments Are Shifting the Narrative for D.R. Horton Stock
summary: D.R. Horton’s fair value estimate has edged down slightly to about $164.69 per share, alongside a modest uptick in the discount rate to roughly 8.74%, as analysts balance a friendlier rate backdrop with softer demand expectations. Revenue growth assumptions have been revised lower to around 4.52%, reflecting concerns that housing activity may respond only gradually to rate cuts despite the company’s scale and execution strengths.
